Geolocation Tracker
ğŸ“Œ Project Overview
This project is a Geolocation Tracker built using Python. It fetches the geolocation of a user or a specified IP address and displays the location on an interactive map in the browser. The application also provides a graphical user interface (GUI) for ease of use.

ğŸ›  Step 1: Set Up Your Environment
- Install Python
- Ensure Python 3.x is installed on your system. You can download it from python.org.
- Install Required Libraries
- Open a terminal or command prompt and run the following commands to install the required libraries: pip install requests folium
- Install a Code Editor
- Install a code editor like Visual Studio Code for writing and running the Python script.

ğŸ›  Step 2: Write the Geolocation Tracker Code
- Create a New Python File
- Create a new Python file named geolocation_tracker.py.

- Write the Code
- Copy and paste the provided Python code into the file. The code includes:

- Fetching geolocation data using the ip-api.com API.
- Displaying the geolocation data in a GUI.
- Opening the location on an interactive map in the browser.

ğŸ›  Step 3: Run the Geolocation Tracker
- Run the Script
- Open the terminal or command prompt, navigate to the directory containing the script, and run: pip install requests folium

Use the Application
- Enter an IP address in the input field (or leave it blank to fetch your own IP's geolocation).
- Click the "Fetch Location" button to display the geolocation data and open the map in your browser.
- Use the "Exit" button to close the application.

ğŸ“Œ Features
Fetches geolocation data for any IP address.
Displays geolocation data (latitude, longitude, city, region, country, and IP).
Opens an interactive map in the browser with the location marked.
User-friendly GUI built with tkinter.

ğŸ“Œ Limitations
The accuracy of the location depends on the IP-based geolocation service (ip-api.com), which may not always be precise.
For better accuracy, consider using a paid geolocation API like Google Maps Geolocation API.

